text: The Roshas caste originates from its close proximity to Sultan Ul Qaum Nawab Jassa Singh Ahluwalia during the middle of the 18th century. This caste is found in both Hindus and Jatt Sikhs of Northern India. Its one of the smallest clans in Jatt Sikhs and belong to Jatt clan Kalal. == References == Category:Indian castes
title: Rosha (subcaste)
